From a6f020d69ded58c8fbd97e43e225ef787fd45813 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: quality-testing-squad <qa@travel-assistant.local>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 18:52:02 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] QA: contract tests for APP-2 (TripPlanInvariants + InMemory
 providers)

24 xUnit tests, 0 skipped, all green. Locks the wire surface that QA
records fixtures against. Covers:

- TripPlanInvariants (14 tests): IATA format, origin!=destination,
  flight time ordering, day-in-range, duplicate dayNumber, activity-on-day,
  totalCost equality + 1c rounding tolerance, EnsureValid throw/no-throw.
- XD-5 grounding rules: Grounded items require sources[]; Pending flights
  cannot emit a flight number. These are merge-gate rules from the
  experience-design-squad.
- InMemoryProviders (7 tests): determinism across calls, price scales
  with travelers, stable ProviderRefId format, Lodging/Activity output
  shape, null-arg defense, ProviderId='InMemory'.

Also wires src/TravelAssistant.Agent.Abstractions and the new test project
into TravelAssistant.slnx so solution-wide build/test picks them up.

Closes a QA contract gate. Call TripPlanInvariants.EnsureValid(plan) in
every provider-driven plan synthesis test going forward.

Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
